                            <p class="mb-4 size-18">Civil engineering encompasses a wide range of sub-disciplines, including structural engineering, environmental engineering, hydraulic engineering, transportation engineering, surveying, construction management, geotechnical engineering and others.</p>
                              <p class="mb-4 size-18">Practicing civil engineers perform a wide variety of functions, including supervision of construction sites, meeting with clients and community members, conducting research, performing calculations, doing design, technical writing, managing projects, budget planning and supervising others. Civil engineers work on building structures, roadway networks, railroads, airports, bridges, harbors, channels, dams, irrigation projects, pipelines, power plants, and water and sewage systems.</p>
                                <p class="mb-4 size-18">Students can get a strong start in this top in-demand field at Marshall University, Huntington, West Virginia, with a Bachelor of Science (BS) degree in Civil Engineering.</p>
                                <p class="mb-4 size-18">There are few degrees that offer such a wide range of opportunities in one field of study. The bachelor’s in Civil Engineering can start your career in this important field, or serve as a good foundation for any other career (e.g., law, science, public policy, environmental protection, government, etc.) that requires strong problem-solving skills, quantitative proficiency, and practice working in multidisciplinary teams to complete complex projects.</p>
                        <h4 class="header-colorize">Why Study Civil Engineering at Marshall?</h4>
                        <p class="mb-4 size-18">At Marshall University, Civil Engineering students receive outstanding personalized attention that’s uncommon among other university engineering programs that typically have large class sizes, graduate assistants doing most of the teaching, and faculty whose primary interest is on research, not teaching.</p>
                        <p class="mb-4 size-18">The bachelor’s degree in Civil Engineering program is designed to fully prepare students for entry into the engineering profession and to become licensed professional engineers. Marshall’s Civil Engineering program is accredited by the Accreditation Board for Engineering and Technology (ABET).</p>
                          <h4>Career Support</h4>
